Emma Stone won the Oscar for best actress on Sunday for the whimsical musical &#8220;La La Land,&#8221; the most honored film of the night.The 28-year-old won her first Oscar in a field that included former winners Meryl Streep and Natalie Portman, as well as Ruth Negga for interracial historical drama &#8220;Loving&#8221; and French actress Isabelle Huppert for rape-revenge thriller &#8220;Elle.&#8221;-AFP